{{Infobox film | name = TechnoCalyps | image = TechnoCalyps DVD cover.jpg | alt = | caption = DVD cover | film name = <!--(for non-English films: film's name in its native language)--> | director = Frank Theys | producer = <!-- or: |producers = --> | writer = Frank Theys | screenplay = | story = | based on = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} --> | starring = | narrator = Jay McMahon | music = Francisco López | cinematography = {{unbulleted list|Phyllis Digneffe|Rian Koopman|Chris Renson}} | editing = {{unbulleted list|Hans Meijer|Frank Theys}} | studio = Votnik | distributor = [[GoDigital Media Group]] | released = {{film date|2006|5||Belgium}} | runtime = 156 minutes | country = Belgium | language = English | budget = | gross = <!--(please use condensed and rounded values, e.g. "£11.6 million" not "£11,586,221")--> }}
'''''TechnoCalyps''''' is a 2006 Belgian [[transhumanism]] documentary film written and directed by [[Frank Theys]]. It explores the advance of technology.<ref name="Agoravox 02-10-14">{{cite news|last1=Man|first1=Blue|title="TechnoCalyps" : en route vers l’apocalypse du transhumanisme|url=http://www.agoravox.tv/tribune-libre/article/technocalyps-en-route-vers-l-43383|accessdate=October 20, 2015|language=French|publisher=[[Agoravox]]|date=February 10, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Quiet Earth 10-06-09"/>
==Documentary precept== Set as a three-part documentary, ''TechnoCalyps'' posits that [[genetics]], [[robotics]], [[artificial intelligence]], [[bionics]], and [[nanotechnology]] seem to be converging towards a goal of having mankind transcend human limits. "director conducts his inquiry into the scientific, ethical and metaphysical dimensions of technological development. The film includes interviews by top experts and thinkers on the subject worldwide".<ref name="The Post-Star 10-15-15">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=TECHNOPALYPS, PART 1"—A Film by Frank Theys|url=http://poststar.com/lifestyles/go/calendar/go-calendar/article_86371f26-c240-5f80-b80a-1b5c617b40cb.html|accessdate=October 20, 2015|publisher=[[The Post-Star]]|date=October 15, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Pijama Surf 04-12-15">{{cite news|last1=Riveroll|first1=Juan Patricio|title=Contrapunto: El sueño de la inmortalidad|url=http://pijamasurf.com/2013/12/contrapunto-el-sueno-de-la-inmortalidad/|accessdate=October 20, 2015|language=Spanish|publisher=Pijama Surf|date=April 12, 2013}}</ref>
==Cast== In the documentary narrated by Jay McMahon, interviewees include: {{div col}} * [[Ian Buruma]] * [[Jean-Jacques Cassiman]] * [[L. Stephen Coles]] * [[Sadaputa Dasa]] * [[Hugo De Garis]] * [[Aubrey de Grey]] * [[Theodore John Kaczynski]] * [[Raymond Kurzweil]] * [[Jeffrey Lichtman]] * [[Ralph C. Merkle]] * [[Marvin Minsky]] * [[Hans Moravec]] * [[Max More]] * [[David F. Noble]] * [[Mark Pesce]] * [[Joe Rosen]] * [[Kirkpatrick Sale]] * [[Anders Sandberg]] * [[Richard Seed]] * [[Bruce Sterling]] * [[Gregory Stock]] * [[Mark W. Tilden]] * [[Frank Tipler]] * [[Margaret Wertheim]] * [[Robert J. White]] * [[Robert Anton Wilson]] * [[Terence McKenna]] * Rael * Osman Bakar * Michel Baudry * Ted Berger * Yang Dan * Thomas B. DeMarse * Anne Foerst * Erin D. Green * Mark Humayun * Hamada Kazuyuki * Carlo Montemagno * [[Natasha Vita-More]] * Jim Yount {{div col end}}
==Reception== ''[[Humanity+|H+ Magazine]]'' wrote that the film focuses "on the various emerging technologies that Transhumanism has coalesced around and feature illuminating (or potentially terrifying) interviews with scientists working in these fields",<ref name="Humanity+ 01-26-13">{{cite news|last1=Jeffery|first1=Scott|title=Producing and Consuming the Posthuman Body in Superhero Narratives|url=http://hplusmagazine.com/2013/01/26/producing-and-consuming-the-posthuman-body-in-superhero-narratives/|accessdate=October 20, 2015|publisher=[[Humanity+|H+ Magazine]]|date=January 26, 2013}}</ref> and ''Crónicas de Esperantia'' wrote that the film was an excellent documentary that shares some future keys.<ref name="Crónicas de Esperantia 03-07-13">{{cite news|last1=Saavedra|first1=Francisco José|title=Technocalyps: el perfeccionamiento humano, un excelente documental que nos muestra algunas claves del futuro de todos nosotros|url=http://www.esperantia.com/2013/03/technocalyps-el-perfeccionamiento.html|accessdate=October 20, 2015|language=Spanish|publisher=Crónicas de Esperantia|date=March 7, 2013}}</ref> Christopher Webster of ''Quiet Earth'' reviewed the documentary and wrote that it "is a really smart look at humanity's quest for immortality through science" and how with its focus on hard science "gets into how this quest effects art and culture and how the whole mess intersects to form the very fabric of who we are."<ref name="Quiet Earth 10-06-09">{{cite news|last1=Webster|first1=Christopher|title=Scientists strive for immortality in Frank Theys' upcoming THE WILL TO VIRTUALITY|url=http://www.quietearth.us/articles/2009/10/06/Scientists-strive-for-immortality-in-Frank-Theys-upcoming-THE-WILL-TO-VIRTUALITY|accessdate=October 20, 2015|publisher=Quiet Earth|date=October 6, 2009}}</ref>
